14 D. Meetings of the Commission.
15 1. All meetings of the Commission that are not closed pursuant
16 to this subsection shall be open to the public. Notice of public
17 meetings shall be posted on the Commission’s website at least thirty
18 (30) days prior to the public meeting.
19 2. Notwithstanding subsection D.1 of this section, the
20 Commission may convene an emergency public meeting by providing at
21 least twenty-four (24) hours’ prior notice on the Commission’s
22 website, and any other means as provided in the Commission’s Rules,
23 for any of the reasons it may dispense with notice of proposed
24 rulemaking under Section 9.L. The Commission’s legal counsel shall
